    <p><strong>Quick Answer:</strong> Cabernet Sauvignon goes with ribeye and strip steak, Pinot Noir works better with filet, and Malbec or Syrah is often the stronger answer when the steak is grilled hard or covered in chimichurri or pepper.</p>
